{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772721890,"nonce":"v9pLZZYkexsRDb/kkL2fwefKvMU=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87wIPzP","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/352","origin":"github"},"title":"Bootstrap script should show sudo commands and skip already-installed packages","message":"## Problem\n\nWhen `make build` triggers the first-run bootstrap (`.agent/scripts/bootstrap.sh`), the script prompts for a `sudo` password without first showing the user what commands will be run. This is a trust issue â€” users shouldn't be asked to enter their password blind.\n\nAdditionally, the script unconditionally runs all installation steps even if the packages are already present. On a system where ROS 2 Jazzy is already installed, the entire bootstrap is unnecessary overhead (and an unnecessary `sudo` prompt).\n\n## Current `sudo` Commands in `bootstrap.sh`\n\nThe script runs 12 `sudo` commands:\n\n| Line | Command | Purpose |\n|------|---------|---------|\n| 14 | `sudo apt update \u0026\u0026 sudo apt install -y locales` | Install locales |\n| 15 | `sudo locale-gen en_US en_US.UTF-8` | Generate UTF-8 locale |\n| 16 | `sudo update-locale LC_ALL=en_US.UTF-8 LANG=en_US.UTF-8` | Set default locale |\n| 26 | `sudo apt install -y software-properties-common` | For `add-apt-repository` |\n| 27 | `sudo add-apt-repository -y universe` | Enable Universe repo |\n| 30 | `sudo apt update \u0026\u0026 sudo apt install -y curl` | Install curl |\n| 46 | `sudo dpkg -i /tmp/ros2-apt-source.deb` | Install ROS 2 apt source |\n| 51 | `sudo apt update` | Update apt cache |\n| 52 | `sudo apt install -y ros-dev-tools` | Install ROS dev tools |\n| 57 | `sudo apt install -y ros-jazzy-ros-base` | Install ROS 2 Jazzy |\n| 64 | `sudo apt install -y python3-pip` | Install pip |\n| 70 | `sudo rosdep init` | Initialize rosdep |\n\n## Proposed Improvements\n\n### 1. Show what will be run before prompting\n\nBefore any `sudo` call, display a summary of all privileged commands that will be executed, so the user can make an informed decision.\n\n### 2. Skip already-installed components\n\nCheck whether each component is already present before attempting to install it:\n\n- **Locale**: check `locale -a | grep -q en_US.utf8`\n- **APT packages**: check `dpkg -s \u003cpackage\u003e 2\u003e/dev/null | grep -q 'Status: install ok installed'`\n- **ROS 2 apt source**: check if `/etc/apt/sources.list.d/` already has the ROS 2 repo\n- **Universe repo**: check `apt-cache policy | grep -q universe`\n- **rosdep init**: check if `/etc/ros/rosdep/sources.list.d/20-default.list` exists\n- **pip packages**: check `python3 -c \"import empy\"` etc.\n\nIf everything is already installed, skip the bootstrap entirely (no `sudo` prompt needed).\n\n### 3. Allow skipping bootstrap explicitly\n\nThe `NONINTERACTIVE=1` and `CI=1` flags suppress the confirmation prompt but still run the commands. There should also be a way to say \"I've already set up my system\" â€” e.g., `touch .make/bootstrap.done` is the current workaround but it's undocumented.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}